### Akeeba Panopticon API — Tasks
###
### Super-user OR `panopticon.admin` on the relevant site for site-scoped tasks.
### System tasks (`site_id` null/0) are super-user only.

@hostname = https://panopticon.local
@token    = REPLACE-ME-WITH-A-REAL-TOKEN

### List all tasks (super-user only)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/tasks?limit=20&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### List tasks for a specific site (site admins may use this scoped form)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/tasks?site_id=1&enabled=1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Read a single task
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/task/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Create a task (PUT)
PUT {{hostname}}/api/v1/task
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "site_id":         1,
  "type":            "joomlaupdate",
  "cron_expression": "0 3 * * *",
  "enabled":         true,
  "params":          {}
}

### Modify an existing task
POST {{hostname}}/api/v1/task/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cron_expression": "30 4 * * *",
  "enabled":         false
}
